The paper discusses measuring properties of complex networks, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the study of social and information networks. cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is less likely but still possible as some complex networks can be related to sound and music. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as it deals with the design and analysis of computer networks. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as they can be related to the analysis and modeling of complex networks.
